24/07/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Three illegal immigrants died and 18 others were injured Thursday (July 23rd) after their van went off the road near Diyarbakir in southeastern Turkey. Police say speeding may have caused the crash. The van was transporting immigrants from Afghanistan and Pakistan who entered Turkey illegally from Iran. The two drivers have been charged in connection with human trafficking. (AFP, MIA - 23/07/09)
